\pard\plain\s21\ql\sb0\sa100\li0\fi0\keep\keepn\b\fs24{}Stomatopoda (Hoplocarida, Malacostraca)\fs20\b0{}
\par\pard\plain\qj\s22\sb0\sa0\li0\fi340\fs20{}\b{}Common name\b0{}. Mantis Shrimps.
\par\pard\plain\qj\s22\sb0\sa0\li0\fi340\fs20{}\b{}Description\b0{}. \b{}Head\b0{}, rostrum present; head, rostrum articulated; eyes stalked; compound, visual elements present; ocular scale present; naupliar eyes absent. \b\i{}Antennules (antenna 1)\i0\b0{} \b\i{}triramous\i0\b0{}; peduncle and flagellum distinct; endopod well developed; exopod well developed, whip-like. Antennae (antenna 2) biramous; exopod multiarticulate and exopod forming a scaphocerite. Mandible uniramous; palp present, or absent. Maxillipeds, 5 pairs; uniramous; second pair greatly enlarged, raptorial. \b{}Thorax\b0{}. \b\i{}Carapace\i0\b0{} present, univalved, \b\i{}enclosing head and anterior thoracic somites\i0\b0{}, dorsoventrally flattened, smooth. Thorax and abdomen differentiated. Peraeopods (legs) 3 pairs; biramous; non-phyllopodous; undifferentiated (simple). Peraeopod 1 (leg 1) simple. Peraeopod 2 (leg 2) simple. Peraeopod 3 (leg 3) simple. \b{}Abdomen\b0{} with 6 somites. Epimera present. Pleopods present, 5 pairs; well developed, broad and flat; pleopod 1 forming a gonopod (eg. petasma) in males. Uropods well developed, 1 pair, positioned ventrolaterally; rami present, exopod with diaresis, partial or complete; endopod without statocyst. Telson present (not fused to pleon).
\par\pard\plain\qj\s22\sb0\sa0\li0\fi340\fs20{}\b{}Larval development\b0{}. Anamorphic. Eggs shed or deposited externally (either carried in a bundle between the maxillipeds or glued to wall of burrow).
\par\pard\plain\qj\s22\sb0\sa0\li0\fi340\fs20{}\b{}Habitat\b0{}. Marine, occasionally brackish.
\par\pard\plain\qj\s22\sb0\sa0\li0\fi340\fs20{}\b{}Distribution\b0{}. Tropical and subtropical seas around the world.
